Package: palat
Type: Package
Title: Generate a Color Pallet from Geographic Coordinates
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Claudia Helena Giraldo Escobar
Maintainer: The package maintainer <claudielena.ge@gmail.com>
Description: This package use the theory of color RGB to assign a color to every point in a data frame.
    The colors change from red at the East to green at the West. 
    The blue increases from North to South.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Imports: utils, ggplot2, rnaturalearth, sf, stats, rworldmap, marmap
